<!-- APPLICATION PROCESS -->

<section class="process" id="process">
  <div class="section-label"><span>How To Enlist</span></div>
  <h2 class="section-heading">THE APPLICATION<br><span>PROCESS</span></h2>
  <div class="process-steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">01</div>
      <div class="step-title">Contact a Recruiter</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Speak with a recruiter who will walk you through options and requirements based on your goals.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">02</div>
      <div class="step-title">Take the ASVAB</div>
      <div class="step-desc">The Armed Services Vocational Aptitude Battery determines your career field eligibility and qualification.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">03</div>
      <div class="step-title">Medical Exam (MEPS)</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Complete a physical exam at a Military Entrance Processing Station to confirm medical eligibility.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">04</div>
      <div class="step-title">Choose Your MOS</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Select your Military Occupational Specialty — your role and career — from available options based on your scores.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">05</div>
      <div class="step-title">Ship to Basic</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Report to basic training and begin your transformation into a military professional.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- APPLICATION FORM -->

<section class="apply-section" id="apply-form">
  <div class="section-label"><span>Enlist Today</span></div>
  <h2 class="section-heading">START YOUR<br><span>APPLICATION</span></h2>
  <div class="apply-grid">
    <div class="apply-info">
      <h3>Ready to Serve?</h3>
      <p>Completing this form connects you with a dedicated recruiter who will guide you through every step — from initial contact to swearing in. There are no fees and no obligations at this stage.</p>
      <p>Before submitting, ensure you meet the basic requirements:</p>
      <ul class="apply-checklist">
        <li>U.S. citizen or legal permanent resident</li>
        <li>17–34 years of age (some roles vary)</li>
        <li>High school diploma or GED</li>
        <li>No disqualifying criminal record</li>
        <li>Physically and medically eligible</li>
        <li>Willing to take the ASVAB test</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <form class="apply-form" id="applyForm" onsubmit="submitForm(event)">
        <div class="form-row">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>First Name *</label>
            <input type="text" placeholder="John" required/>
          </div>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>Last Name *</label>
            <input type="text" placeholder="Smith" required/>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-row">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>Date of Birth *</label>
            <input type="date" required/>
          </div>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>Phone Number *</label>
            <input type="tel" placeholder="(555) 000-0000" required/>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Email Address *</label>
          <input type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required/>
        </div>
        <div class="form-row">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>State of Residence *</label>
            <select required>
              <option value="">Select State</option>
              <option>Alabama</option><option>Alaska</option><option>Arizona</option><option>Arkansas</option>
              <option>California</option><option>Colorado</option><option>Connecticut</option><option>Delaware</option>
              <option>Florida</option><option>Georgia</option><option>Hawaii</option><option>Idaho</option>
              <option>Illinois</option><option>Indiana</option><option>Iowa</option><option>Kansas</option>
              <option>Kentucky</option><option>Louisiana</option><option>Maine</option><option>Maryland</option>
              <option>Massachusetts</option><option>Michigan</option><option>Minnesota</option><option>Mississippi</option>
              <option>Missouri</option><option>Montana</option><option>Nebraska</option><option>Nevada</option>
              <option>New Hampshire</option><option>New Jersey</option><option>New Mexico</option><option>New York</option>
              <option>North Carolina</option><option>North Dakota</option><option>Ohio</option><option>Oklahoma</option>
              <option>Oregon</option><option>Pennsylvania</option><option>Rhode Island</option><option>South Carolina</option>
              <option>South Dakota</option><option>Tennessee</option><option>Texas</option><option>Utah</option>
              <option>Vermont</option><option>Virginia</option><option>Washington</option><option>West Virginia</option>
              <option>Wisconsin</option><option>Wyoming</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>Education Level *</label>
            <select required>
              <option value="">Select Level</option>
              <option>High School Diploma</option>
              <option>GED</option>
              <option>Some College</option>
              <option>Associate's Degree</option>
              <option>Bachelor's Degree</option>
              <option>Graduate Degree</option>
            </select>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Branch of Interest</label>
          <select>
            <option value="">No Preference</option>
            <option>U.S. Army</option>
            <option>U.S. Navy</option>
            <option>U.S. Marine Corps</option>
            <option>U.S. Air Force</option>
            <option>U.S. Space Force</option>
            <option>U.S. Coast Guard</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Questions or Comments</label>
          <textarea placeholder="Any questions for your recruiter?"></textarea>
        </div>
        <button type="submit" class="form-submit">Submit Application →</button>
        <p class="form-note">By submitting you agree to be contacted by a military recruiter. Enlistment is free — there are no application fees of any kind.</p>
      </form>
      <div class="form-success" id="formSuccess">
        <h4>Application Received!</h4>
        <p>A recruiter will contact you within 1–2 business days. Thank you for your interest in serving.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CITIZENSHIP / GREEN CARD -->

<section class="citizenship" id="citizenship">
  <div class="section-label"><span>Pathways to Citizenship</span></div>
  <h2 class="section-heading">MILITARY SERVICE &<br><span>U.S. CITIZENSHIP</span></h2>
  <div class="citizenship-grid">
    <div class="citizenship-img">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521295121783-8a321d551ad2?w=800&q=80" alt="American flag ceremony"/>
      <div class="citizenship-img-label">Naturalization Ceremony</div>
    </div>
    <div class="citizenship-content">
      <p>Military service is one of the most honored pathways to U.S. citizenship. Non-citizens who serve honorably may be eligible for expedited naturalization under Section 329 of the Immigration and Nationality Act (INA).</p>

```
  <div class="citizenship-path">
    <h4>Naturalization During Peacetime (INA § 328)</h4>
    <p>Legal permanent residents (green card holders) who have served at least one year on active duty may apply for naturalization — with reduced physical presence requirements.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="citizenship-path">
    <h4>Expedited Naturalization During Hostilities (INA § 329)</h4>
    <p>Non-citizens who serve honorably during a designated period of hostilities may apply for citizenship immediately upon enlistment — waiving the typical residency waiting periods.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="citizenship-path">
    <h4>Green Card (LPR) Through Service</h4>
    <p>Certain military visa programs (such as MAVNI — Military Accessions Vital to the National Interest) have historically allowed enlistment in exchange for lawful permanent residency. Availability varies; speak with a recruiter for current program status.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="citizenship-note">
    <strong>Important:</strong> All immigration and naturalization benefits through the military are provided by the U.S. government at <strong>no cost to the service member</strong>. There are no application fees charged by military recruiters. For official information, visit <strong>uscis.gov</strong> or consult a licensed immigration attorney.
  </div>
</div>
```

  </div>
</section>

